&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Deputy Medical Director is a newly created post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This substantive role is being created to support the Medical Director in a number of areas, as detailed below, and to provide enhanced clinical leadership to the Trust. It is important for the Trust to strengthen key relationships with external stakeholders, particularly CCG’s, and having senior clinician input to these relationships is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In addition, within the organisation, there is a need to improve communication and engagement with senior clinicians.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The deputy Medical Director will help to strengthen this communication, and work with senior colleagues to develop greater engagement in the Trust’s clinical strategic objectives, as well as championing evidence based medicine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is open to medical consultants, who possess the experience at or near board level and have also worked in medical leadership roles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Mehdi Veisi, Medical Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mehdi.veisi@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;020 8702 4488&lt;/p&gt;
